Partial rv of last edit: 1. Don't squeeze too much info into the infobox. There is no consensus about this matter, so "unclassified" does the job. 2. Both sources are blogs, thus not peer-reviewed reliable sources. 3. The first blog actually reports about Blasco Ferrer (2010), which is already cited in the main text, so no need to duplicate. 4. The second blog cites a paper which is not about language relations. 5. None of these sources uses the term "Vasconic".
